{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":417349,"duration_api_ms":414878,"num_turns":42,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"d53262dd-a71f-4a25-a14b-0ab34feffd9a","total_cost_usd":2.2270015,"usage":{"input_tokens":34,"cache_creation_input_tokens":100988,"cache_read_input_tokens":2366763,"output_tokens":16491,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":93992,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6996},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":34,"outputTokens":16491,"cacheReadInputTokens":2366763,"cacheCreationInputTokens":100988,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":2.2270015,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"Reviewed the full diff (911 insertions across 24 files) implementing retry hardening, timeout enforcement, backoff with jitter, and BinaryNotFound classification. The changes are well-structured and comprehensive. All key acceptance criteria are met: increased retry limits, hard timeout enforcement in both process_backend and tmux adapters, exit 127 → BinaryNotFound (terminal), exponential backoff with jitter, and good test coverage. I found one minor robustness issue and the rest is solid.","amendments":[{"body":"In `src/contexts/agent_execution/service.rs:210`, `request.timeout + Duration::from_secs(30)` uses `Duration::add` which panics on overflow. Replace with `request.timeout.saturating_add(Duration::from_secs(30))` to prevent a panic if a timeout value near `Duration::MAX` is ever passed. While practically unlikely with real timeout values, this is a one-character fix that eliminates a theoretical panic path in production code.","rationale":"Duration::add delegates to checked_add().expect() which panics on overflow. All other duration arithmetic in the retry policy already uses saturating operations (saturating_mul, saturating_pow). The service timeout computation should be consistent."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"461dbf55-919b-4b9e-83fd-ba34602f3396"}
